    </p>

    <h3>Dec 11–12, 2022 — Margaret Bird letter and John A. Charles testimony to the State Land Board</h3>
    <p>
      Written submission and in-person testimony to the State Land Board on the
      eve of the December 2022 votes on the Elliott. Margaret Bird, a school
      trust lands scholar, addressed the fiduciary framework; John A. Charles
      of the Cascade Policy Institute addressed financial and policy
      considerations.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1WKIbVtFp7vzqJkZzyt8Kn4kvI94DgeQL/view?usp=drive_link" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Charles testimony (PDF) →</a>
    </p>

    <h3>Oct 13, 2023 — Geoff Huntington (Governor's Office) policy memo</h3>
    <p>
      Internal policy memorandum from the Governor's natural-resources staff on
